a lifetime.

14:54.325 --> 14:58.729
It must be lastin'
somebody else's lifetime.
We got ballpoint pens.

14:58.797 --> 15:00.731
Look at this stationery.
"Hercules plumbing" ?

15:00.799 --> 15:04.334
That's the company
I used to work for
before we was married.

15:05.403 --> 15:07.337
And you saved this, huh ?

15:07.405 --> 15:10.340
And our embossed stationery
with the initials
intertwined at the top,

15:10.408 --> 15:12.142
there it is, gone.

15:12.210 --> 15:15.145
Maybe it'll get
to the president faster...

15:15.213 --> 15:17.915
If they think you own
a plumbing company.

15:17.983 --> 15:19.917
You're a dingbat.

15:19.985 --> 15:23.687
Let me get started.
You go over there and finish
pastin' your tradin' stamps.

15:23.755 --> 15:27.691
That's a good idea.
I got almost enough
to fill another book.

15:27.759 --> 15:31.161
If we get three
and a half books,
I can buy that bathroom scale.

15:31.229 --> 15:33.864
Edith, please.

15:33.932 --> 15:35.866
I hope the kids are out.

15:35.934 --> 15:39.202
Don't worry.
They went for a long walk.

15:39.270 --> 15:41.539
Nobody's here
to bother you.

15:43.474 --> 15:45.910
<i>You'll have</i>
<i>absolute silence.</i>

15:49.213 --> 15:51.649
Perfect quiet.

15:51.716 --> 15:54.384
<i>Nobody goin'</i>
<i>back and forth.</i>

15:54.452 --> 15:56.386
<i>Nobody talk-talk--</i>

16:02.226 --> 16:04.962
dear Mr. president,

16:05.030 --> 16:07.464
your honor,

16:07.532 --> 16:09.466
sir--

16:10.936 --> 16:12.870
dear Mr. president,

16:19.177 --> 16:21.111
your honor,

16:21.179 --> 16:23.146
[ bang ]

16:24.515 --> 16:26.450
Sir--
<i>[ Two bangs ]</i>

16:26.517 --> 16:29.787
Will you stop
lickin' and bangin'
over there ?

16:29.854 --> 16:33.356
<i>[ Bang ]</i>
<i>Oh, you're breakin' up</i>
<i>my whole concentration !</i>

16:33.424 --> 16:36.393
Oh, I'm sorry.
What have you
got down so far ?

16:38.262 --> 16:41.098
"Dear Mr. president,
your honor, sir."

16:41.165 --> 16:43.533
Yeah, go on.

16:43.602 --> 16:48.171
How much more
do you expect me to do with you
lickin' and bangin' over there ?

16:48.239 --> 16:51.541
Here, I got a good idea.
You come over here.
Come here.

16:51.610 --> 16:53.443
Yeah, come on over.

16:53.511 --> 16:55.445
Now, you sit down there...

16:55.513 --> 16:57.447
And you write
what I dictate.

16:57.515 --> 16:59.449
Oh, Archie,
oh, I don't know.

16:59.517 --> 17:01.451
I'm too nervous.
It's to the president.

17:01.519 --> 17:03.453
What are you
nervous about ?

17:03.521 --> 17:05.955
I'm gonna do
the whole thing.
Go ahead.

17:06.023 --> 17:08.458
You just write
what I tell ya.

17:08.526 --> 17:10.961
What do you got
there ?
Nothin'.

17:11.029 --> 17:13.964
What do you mean ?
I wrote a whole
introduction.

17:16.300 --> 17:18.234
"Dear Mr. president,
your honor, sir."

17:18.301 --> 17:20.237
Oh, that--
that's lousy.

17:20.304 --> 17:23.007
What ?
What you read.

17:23.074 --> 17:27.377
That's what you wrote.
I know, but you read it
so rotten !

17:27.444 --> 17:29.379
I think
it was the words.

17:29.447 --> 17:31.882
Read them same words
over again.

17:31.950 --> 17:34.885
Read 'em with
a little feeling, huh ?
Go ahead.

17:37.388 --> 17:40.991
[ With feeling ]
"Dear Mr. president,

17:41.059 --> 17:43.193
your honor, sir."

17:43.261 --> 17:45.395
Yes !
Beautiful words.

17:45.463 --> 17:49.499
I only hope Mr. Nixon
reads 'em that way.

17:49.567 --> 17:51.501
Oh, Edith, please,
will ya !

17:51.569 --> 17:54.504
It's tough enough writin'
a letter to the top man
in the whole free world,

17:54.572 --> 17:57.507
so just stifle your comments
and write what I tell ya.

17:57.575 --> 18:01.111
Dear Mr. president,
your honor, sir,

18:01.179 --> 18:04.782
uh, as one of your
faithful constitutionals,

18:04.849 --> 18:06.784
I--

18:06.851 --> 18:10.287
no, no, that's wrong.
That's wrong, that's wrong.

18:10.354 --> 18:13.256
Uh, read it back to me
again.

18:16.061 --> 18:18.495
[ With feeling ]
"Dear Mr. president--"

18:18.563 --> 18:20.998
jump over that
and read the new stuff !

18:22.333 --> 18:25.268
"As one of your
faithful constitutionals--"

18:25.336 --> 18:27.270
wrong !
What ?

18:27.338 --> 18:30.607
The word is wrong !
Why did you write it down ?
<i>[ Doorbell rings ]</i>

18:30.675 --> 18:32.609
There's somebody
at the door.

18:32.677 --> 18:34.611
Go on, answer the bell.
Let me in there.

18:34.679 --> 18:38.115
And no matter who it is,
we ain't home, huh ?

18:49.094 --> 18:54.464
How am I gonna tell 'em
we ain't home if I'm
standin' there talkin' to 'em ?

19:00.004 --> 19:01.939
Try.

19:05.176 --> 19:08.112
Good afternoon.
Oh, good afternoon,
sister.

19:08.179 --> 19:10.313
We're collecting money...

19:10.381 --> 19:13.383
For the St. januarius
underprivileged
children's hospital.

19:13.451 --> 19:16.386
Oh, I think my husband
gave at the office.

19:16.454 --> 19:19.890
Uh, we don't solicit aid
in commercial institutions.

19:19.958 --> 19:21.892
Just neighborhoods,
families.

19:21.960 --> 19:23.894
Oh, I see.

19:23.962 --> 19:27.697
Archie, the sister
is collecting for the
underprivileged children.

19:27.766 --> 19:30.400
I gave at the office.

19:30.468 --> 19:34.571
It must've been
a different nun.
You do look alike.

19:37.308 --> 19:42.312
Edith, come over here.
I need some help.
I'm searching for a word.

19:42.380 --> 19:44.915
He's searching
for a word.

19:44.983 --> 19:46.917
Maybe the sister
could help you !

19:46.985 --> 19:50.420
Ahh-- yeah.
Maybe she could at that.

19:50.488 --> 19:53.957
Uh, uh, come on in, sister.
Step right in.

19:54.025 --> 19:56.960
Get out of the way,
Edith.

19:57.028 --> 20:01.098
Hi, sister.
I bet you was wonderin'
what I was doing at the table.

20:01.166 --> 20:04.601
No, actually I was--
well, in case you was
wonderin' what I was doin'--

20:04.669 --> 20:06.904
I wasn't.
Now, if you'll--

20:06.971 --> 20:10.240
would you let me tell you
what I was doin' over there
at the table ?

20:11.776 --> 20:15.212
I was writin' a letter
to the president
of the United States...

20:15.280 --> 20:19.216
To fill him in on how
the people of this neighborhood
are thinkin' and feelin'.

20:19.284 --> 20:23.220
Yes, well, I'm sure
you know the feelings...

20:23.288 --> 20:25.722
Of this particular
constituency.

20:25.790 --> 20:28.158
That's the word.
Thank you, sister.

20:28.226 --> 20:30.160
I gotta get back to work.

20:30.228 --> 20:33.163
Edith, give the sister
a generous contribution.

20:33.231 --> 20:36.166
Edith, just a minute.
Before you do,
come over here.

20:36.234 --> 20:38.668
Nothin' more
than half a buck.

20:38.736 --> 20:42.172
No matter what they tell ya,
most of what you give 'em,

20:42.240 --> 20:44.208
they buy golden candlesticks
with it.

20:55.619 --> 20:57.554
Edith.

20:59.090 --> 21:02.025
Edith, this is gonna be good.
You know that ?

21:03.527 --> 21:05.462
Yeah.

21:05.529 --> 21:08.465
I think Mr. Nixon
is gonna love this.

21:17.108 --> 21:20.543
[ Man ] Ladies and gentlemen,
from the east room
of the white house,

21:20.611 --> 21:22.545
the president
of the United States.

21:22.613 --> 21:26.049
[ Applause ]
♪ [ Piano: Processional ]

21:32.123 --> 21:34.557
[ Tv: President Nixon ]
My fellow Americans,

21:34.625 --> 21:38.395
tonight I want to read you
a letter I've just received
from a private citizen.

21:38.462 --> 21:42.099
<i>It starts, of course,</i>
<i>with a highly proper...</i>

21:42.166 --> 21:45.769
<i>"Dear Mr. president,</i>
<i> </i> <i>your honor, sir."</i>

21:47.138 --> 21:50.374
<i>Now let me make one thing</i>
<i>perfectly clear.</i>

21:50.441 --> 21:52.876
<i>I</i> love
<i>that beginning.</i>

21:54.245 --> 21:56.413
<i>This citizen writes,</i>
<i>and I quote:</i>

21:56.480 --> 22:01.885
"I personally don't agree
with all the 'confregration'
on the college campuses...

22:01.953 --> 22:03.887
"Or them ecology nuts...

22:03.955 --> 22:08.125
"Who only see disaster
in this great country of ours.

22:08.192 --> 22:11.461
"But like Duke Wayne would say,

22:11.529 --> 22:15.132
"we came up off the mat before
when the goin' was tough,

22:15.199 --> 22:18.135
<i>"and I know so long</i>
<i> </i> <i>as we all work together,</i>

22:18.202 --> 22:20.137
<i>"this nation under God...</i>

22:20.204 --> 22:22.139
<i>"Shall not diminish</i>
<i> </i> <i>from the earth.</i>

22:23.374 --> 22:26.476
"Anyway, my regards
to your vice, Mr. agnew.

22:28.947 --> 22:31.448
"And special regards...

22:31.515 --> 22:34.784
"To Mrs. Nixon and tricia,

22:34.852 --> 22:38.021
"who I know you wouldn't
let drink no water...

22:38.089 --> 22:40.190
Exceptin' the best."

22:40.258 --> 22:44.894
This terrific letter
was written by
Mr. Archie bunker,

22:44.963 --> 22:47.064
and in your president's
opinion,

22:47.131 --> 22:49.066
Archie bunker is...

22:49.133 --> 22:53.036
One... great... American.

22:53.104 --> 22:56.039
[ Tv: Applause ]

23:04.248 --> 23:06.183
<i>[ Door opens ]</i>
<i>You finish your letter</i>
<i>yet, daddy ?</i>

23:06.250 --> 23:09.186
You had enough time
to write the whole congress.

23:09.253 --> 23:11.188
You keep your pants on,
hotshot.

23:11.255 --> 23:14.691
This just might be
the best letter that was
ever wrote to a president.

23:14.758 --> 23:17.694
Good.
Let's go mail 'em.
Oh, no, you don't.

23:17.761 --> 23:20.697
If anybody mails these,
it's gonna be me.
Why don't we both go ?

23:20.764 --> 23:23.700
It's only a block.
We'll all go.

23:23.767 --> 23:25.702
Yeah, I figured
we would.

23:25.769 --> 23:27.704
Just imagine.

23:27.771 --> 23:30.707
Two letters to the president
from one house.

23:30.774 --> 23:33.910
That don't happen every day.
We'd better get going.
Let's go.

23:33.978 --> 23:36.980
Now, wait a minute.
Hold your horses, everybody.

23:37.048 --> 23:38.982
[ Chuckles ]

23:39.050 --> 23:41.485
Oh, Archie, you go first.
Here.

23:41.552 --> 23:44.488
Come on.
The last pickup is 4:30.
We'll be late.

24:03.474 --> 24:05.909
That was so thrilling.

24:08.146 --> 24:11.681
Imagine, two letters
to the president...

24:11.749 --> 24:13.683
From the same house.

24:13.751 --> 24:17.087
Every American ought to
write to his president.

24:17.155 --> 24:19.589
Yeah. It feels good
being a citizen.

24:19.657 --> 24:22.125
It's wonderful
to be involved.

24:24.395 --> 24:26.329
Archie.
Mmm ?

24:26.397 --> 24:28.331
Did you jiggle ?
What ?

24:28.399 --> 24:30.833
The mailbox.
You put the letters in.

24:30.901 --> 24:32.835
Afterwards,
did you jiggle ?

24:32.903 --> 24:35.338
Certainly I jiggled--

24:35.406 --> 24:37.607
wait a minute.

24:37.675 --> 24:40.843
I-- no, uh--

24:40.911 --> 24:42.845
did either of youse two
jiggle ?

24:42.913 --> 24:45.348
I didn't jiggle.
I thought you jiggled,
daddy.

24:45.416 --> 24:49.152
Well, I always did
all my life,
but I don't know.

24:49.220 --> 24:52.655
Edith, what do you think
we oughta do ?

24:52.723 --> 24:55.225
I think
we'd better go jiggle.

24:55.293 --> 24:58.228
Why didn't you jiggle,
meathead ?
You put the letters in the box !

24:58.296 --> 25:02.732
Can't I rely on you
to do nothin' right ?
The man that mails, jiggles !

25:17.248 --> 25:20.783
[ Archie ]
♪ boy, the way
Glenn Miller played ♪

25:20.851 --> 25:24.921
[ Edith ]
♪ songs that made
the hit parade ♪

25:24.989 --> 25:28.325
[ Archie ]
♪ guys like us
we had it made ♪

25:28.392 --> 25:33.163
[ Archie, Edith ]
♪ those were the days ♪

